            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "1W0oe",
              "x": 99,
              "y": -173,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay this is an exploration of different physics effects that we could potentially apply to the node and the knowledge graph itself. I think in the current build we have a really nice motif for the treatment of connector lines and this is a persistently animated dashed line. I don't want to necessarily lose that mechanic as I think it does a really nice job of communicating data being passed between the nodes.\n\nI've deleted actually all the other subframes within this subframe, if that makes sense, and I've left only one, which is v6 gravity. I think it might be interesting to explore giving the connector lines a bit of physics weight so that they don't feel like stiff static lines. Instead they feel like rope or some more flexible malleable material that might be influenced by the imaginary gravity of the environment. "
            }
          ]
        },
