              "name": "conceptNote",
              "fill": "#555550",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 740,
              "content": "Eliminates the separate context menu entirely — actions live ON the node.",
              "fontFamily": "Inconsolata",
              "fontSize": 10,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "O1OBr",
              "x": 510,
              "y": -69,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay here's a study for the node in its Hubbard focus state, where we were exploring different patterns by which, when a node is engaged and in a focus state, it might reveal a sub-menu associated with the actions you can take per node. I happen to particularly like V1, which is cardinal points. This is the idea that when hovered on the node, it will expose a series of controls where the user would have an understanding that they could take specific actions for each node. "
            }
          ]
        },
