            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "HQdUx",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 515,
              "y": -109,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay don't need to be long-winded here. I thought this was a valuable study of what a hover-to-reveal tool tip like card would reveal some portion of the prompt, either added by the human user or the response added by the AI model.\n\nI think one thing to bear in mind is that we're using a blue-purple indicator dot to represent activity added by, in this case, Claude, and that blue-purple tone is off-brand. If we do end up denoting the activity of a model, we'd want to use our brand red and not that blue-purple.\n\nOverall I think this is a really strong representation of what those tool tip cards could look like and I do like that they have a line connecting the tool tip to the node itself. "
            }
          ]
        },
