                },
                {
                  "type": "note",
                  "id": "CACII",
                  "x": 375,
                  "y": -402,
                  "width": 250,
                  "height": 219,
                  "content": "Okay this frame is basically showcasing some of the thinking about how we could implement analog controls using the keyboard to navigate the memory graph and select different nodes. I think some of the thinking here is valid but this feels unresolved. This is an aspect of what we designed earlier that I think we need to take a look back at and solidify the thinking around. Ideally what we would be introducing is the logic by which you could influence directional keys on your keyboard to navigate the memory graph and select different nodes within the graph.\n\nThere might be additional opportunities to add keyboard controls or hot keys that could be sort of like shortcuts to taking key actions across the system but I'm less concerned with that than I am with actually navigating the knowledge graph by influencing the directional keys. Both concepts are valid but I think this needs a little bit more work and needs to be a bit more resolved before we can include it within the system. I would imagine also that there should be some way to reveal the keyboard options because I think there will be a need to demystify that for the user who might not expect that that's available to them. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
