              "fontWeight": "600",
              "letterSpacing": 1.2
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "8zGgH",
              "name": "subtitle",
              "fill": "#404040",
              "content": "Annotated connections — type, time, tokens, direction",
              "fontFamily": "Inconsolata",
              "fontSize": 10,
              "fontWeight": "normal",
              "letterSpacing": 0.5
            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "qD7Xm",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 860,
              "y": -175,
              "width": 247,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay cool, this was another case study where we were looking at the edge labels and the treatment of the connector lines. I think a lot of the thinking here is sound and valid. I particularly appreciate the minimal nature by which you executed this.\n\nI think it's very valid to show an expression of how many tokens were spent bridging a connection between two nodes. I also think some of the time values, in terms of time spent between two nodes in the process of the model thinking, are valid. I also like the simple directional chevron added in the center of the line, denoting where data is flowing from and to. I think this concept is very strong and the way that we've visualized it is also very strong. I again happen to particularly like that we did it in a very minimal way. "
            },
