            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "TjQzh",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 538,
              "y": -110,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay this study is super cool. I'm not going to make this long-winded but effectively the stage three and stage four solutions that show a locked state or an additional modal that could be used for a focus state or a hover state is quite cool. I think it also does start bleeding into and lending itself to the way that we will animate the nodes when they are generated in a focus state etc. so I think some of the thinking here is valid. I'd carry it forward and continue to explore. "
            }
          ]
        },
