              "id": "sOjHs",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 879,
              "y": -64,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay again here, I think we were continuing to explore how to articulate the state of different nodes visually and I think once again we came to a really nice result where there's a progressive enhancement of the node as it either is enacted and continually acted upon. I like the progressive nature of this study.\n\nThe one thing that I would just caveat is that we're using the wrong brand color here. We want to bring this back into the world of our design system but then also sort of carry forward the good logic of the way the nature of this study is expressing that the nodes evolve over time and evolve in reaction to activity against them. "
            }
          ]
