                  "name": "Z3 Node Title",
                  "fill": "#c8956c",
                  "content": "Why do LLMs hallucinate?",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "600"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "THvUV",
                  "x": 16,
                  "y": 40,
                  "name": "Z3 Response Body",
                  "fill": "#808080",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": 168,
                  "content": "LLMs hallucinate because they optimize for plausibility rather than truth. The model generates tokens based on statistical likelihood given the training distribution, not by consulting a ground-truth knowledge base. When the prompt falls outside well-represented training data, the model confabulates — producing fluent, confident, and wrong output.",
