        {
          "type": "note",
          "id": "XlYf3",
          "x": 1887.1951784589291,
          "y": 131.67895551200309,
          "width": 281,
          "height": 289,
          "content": "Okay so collected on this frame are three subframes. Each one addresses the design system foundations. These subframes include design tokens, as well as a color palette and specificity around the use of typography. What I'd like to do is unify these. I think they all stand to demonstrate the intention for the design system well but what we'd like to do is unify those three subframes and make one master version.\n\nThis master version should address:\nspacing\nborder radius\nthe glass treatment\nany other material or tactile effects that we have created\nAdditionally we should address typography from a typeface selection standpoint as well as a scaling and usage standpoint. We should also address the color palette, the elevation stack, and any other detail that would help us reinforce the material design logic that we've applied to the design system and its many components."
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "id": "yjJzn",
          "x": 1067,
          "y": 246,
          "width": 250,
          "height": 219,
          "content": "From a composition standpoint this frame is probably the closest to what I expect from a design system documentation standpoint. I would use this frame as the sterling example of the type of output that is expected from this exercise of finalizing and perfecting documentation associated with the design system foundations. It would be really a question of you pulling reference from both this frame and the frame directly below it. "
        }
      ]
    },
