              "y": 75,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay, conversely, this is closer to the correct execution. Again this was an exercise where we're studying the multi-state of the input field and how we can bolster its dynamicism and how it visually indicates to the user that it has engaged in this state change as it's working, streaming, collecting a prompt from the user, etc. This is a bit closer to the final state but I think there's a variety of states we haven't accounted for and there's a bit of thinking to do around how to finalize this treatment of the input field. "
            }
