              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay to not be long-winded, here was another study of the input field and its dynamic multi-state execution. I think it is maybe closer in some regard to the inclusion of the base tones from our design system that work or the design system applied to the components that we should be seeing as canonical.\n\nI think with this direction we're overusing the beige or peach color and that is incorrect as obviously the red red value is the core brand accent color. I think one thing that we're doing really good here is that in its idle state the input field is smaller in its horizontal orientation. When it's active it grows in horizontal length to feel a bit more substantial as a component within the larger system as we're viewing these components in the browser Chrome. "
            }
          ]
        },
