            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "Lf0S4",
              "x": 1275,
              "y": 119,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay this subframe is a collection of a variety of design components. I would say if there was one subframe within this collection of design component studies, this frame would stand to represent the closest to final version of the treatment of components. I would pay particularly close attention to the styling and the guidelines that have been added to this frame. The idea is that this is the closest to the final styling.\n\nOne caveat is that I think we can quickly begin to overuse the peach value, which is meant to be very tertiary to the system. The system is meant to be led with the red value, which is truly the single brand accent color, and the peach or cream color is meant to be used much more sparingly than the base layer tones and the brand red. "
            }
          ]
        },
