                {
                  "type": "note",
                  "id": "ebIix",
                  "layoutPosition": "absolute",
                  "x": 900,
                  "y": -172,
                  "width": 250,
                  "height": 219,
                  "content": "Okay this frame also follows suit from the first frame, which I recommended we should consider as the closest to final versions of the components. We've also done a good job of carrying that styling forward into this study of the session pill. Essentially the idea of this component is that I'm able to influence the base component to produce a drop-down menu and then be able to navigate between active sessions. I think we'd also want an opportunity to create a new session or add a new session. A lot of that is handled here.\n\nI think there's more of an objective for this component to just work to finalize it. Consider whatever that means. I think the other piece of this is considering whether or not we should have any search functionality. By natural language query should the user be able to search through past sessions? I'm also thinking a bit about how the idea of clipping part of the memory graph to create a new session should be denoted. That might be something we want to handle within this drop-down menu; that might not be but I think that is sort of the crux of the exploration for this particular component. "
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "FdsSS",
                  "name": "Peek Column",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 16,
                  "children": [
