            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "UEZ8a",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 634,
              "y": 147,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay so I kept this frame in because I think there's a lot of good that we've done when exploring this particular component. A couple of key things to mention are:\nThis component design study is not actually leveraging the correct treatment of components that I identified as correctly generated in the first two subfields (frames that I left notes on).\nWhat this component study is doing well is really beginning to spell out the different states of a menu and the menu that would result from a search query. We're covering topics like type ahead when the model is working or streaming and then also the concept of branching.\nI think a big caveat here is that we're using the wrong brand colors and we may be accounting for states that either we don't need or that we need to evolve beyond this point."
            },
