            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "TvSag",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 814,
              "y": 0,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay with similar fashion to the last note that I left on the subframe that was just above this one, I think we're doing a lot of good in this study but we're also not carrying forward the correct version of the interface design style that we want to perpetuate across the entire final collection of components.\n\nAgain what we are doing correctly here is exploring this idea of introducing custom slash commands within the input field. This is similar to the conceptual territory of querying with natural language and seeing type ahead. I think these are both valid conceptually and we want to carry them forward and also iron out the final visual treatment of the interface to support these features. "
            }
          ]
        },
