                        },
                        {
                          "type": "note",
                          "id": "YVtpi",
                          "width": 250,
                          "height": 219,
                          "content": "I happen to like some of these studies of the breadcrumb indicator. This is an important component as it provides wayfinding details to a user and it gives them contextual grounding in what state of the application they are in at any given time. This is a relatively important component to figure out and make sure that we build correctly and to make it so it is hard working for the user.\n\nI think these studies were interesting. They are hyper minimal, which is the design language that we're trying to perpetuate but I don't think that we got to a final resolve here. I think this component deserves a bit more study and research. "
                        }
                      ]
