            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "JdgRC",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 1261,
              "y": 22,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "I really like this density strip study. I think what it's trying to articulate is the timeline by which the memory graph was created and where there were spikes of activity throughout that timeline. I like the study generally. I think it is steering into the correct territory in terms of brand expression; however I don't think that we nailed this and it's not explicit enough to where I am certain about what it's displaying. Even in my response to you here in this note, I am uncertain as to what I'm looking at but it does look interesting and I'd like to continue to explore it if I got the conceptual direction correct. If not, please reply in prompt and let me know that I got it wrong."
            }
          ]
        },
