                    {
                      "type": "note",
                      "id": "AJ2Wx",
                      "layoutPosition": "absolute",
                      "x": 488,
                      "y": -159,
                      "width": 250,
                      "height": 219,
                      "content": "Again I think this is an interesting exploration but we're using the wrong brand application. This does not map well to the canonical versions of the components that I've identified throughout this session of note taking. Additionally I'm not sure at what point I would see a comparison between two clipped memory graphs and so I'm just not sure where you're envisioning this to actually appear within the system. I think the concept of comparing the different graphs is interesting. I just can't really think of a core use case as to why we would introduce this into the system.\n\nBeyond that I think the idea of where the clippings maybe are saved as memory is an interesting territory to explore. I just don't really understand how we got here. Again we're using the wrong brand colors. We want to make sure that the components we generate in this next session align perfectly to the canonical versions of the components that I've identified. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
