            {
              "type": "note",
              "id": "BFbUt",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": 275,
              "y": 0,
              "width": 250,
              "height": 219,
              "content": "Okay this drop-down menu is super cool. This is definitely a problem that I erred on expressing that we need to solve for, and that is sort of the need for the user to return and access past clippings and there be some written record of those clippings. A clipping is a subsection that is extracted from a larger memory graph and it is a subsection that the user might opt to start a new session with or save as memory. Therefore they will need to return to their list of clippings and be able to understand the history of the actions they took. Now in terms of the execution I think we're a little far away from the brand design style but I'd like to explore bolstering this and improving the visual craft so it feels like it is part of our design system. I'd also like to explore where this lives within the main states of the application and whether there is any other treatment from a design perspective that we could apply to a component like this that would be equally as valuable as this."
            }
          ]
        },
